olive oil
1 portion cauliflower
1 sachet Berbere seasoning
1 packet garlic paste
1 tbs honey
1 packet Chopped Veggie Mix
1 packet pistachios
1 packet Israeli couscous
1.25 cup water
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 bag baby spinach leaves
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 bunch mint

Preheat the oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut the cauliflower so you get
two pieces per person. In a large bowl, add the Berbere spice blend, garlic
paste, honey, a splash of water and a drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and
pepper. Add the cauliflower and toss to combine. Place the cauliflower on
a lined oven tray. Place the chopped veggie mix and a drizzle of olive oil on
a second lined oven tray, then season with salt and paper. Toss to coat, then
roast the cauliflower and veggies, until tender and charred, 25-30 minutes.
In the last 5 minutes of cook time, add the pistachios to the side of the tray
with the veggie mix and roast until toasted.

While the veggies are roasting, heat a large saucepan over a medium-high
heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Add the Israeli couscous and toast, stirring
occasionally, until golden, 1 minute. Add the water and vegetable stock
powder. Reduce the heat to medium and simmer until the couscous is tender
and the water has absorbed, 10-12 minutes.
TIP: Add a splash of water if the couscous seems dry

Add the baby spinach leaves and the roasted veggie mix to the cooked
couscous. Season to taste.

Divide the roast veggie Israeli couscous between plates and top with the
Berbere-roasted cauliflower. Spoon over the Greek-style yoghurt. Tear over
the mint leaves and sprinkle with the toasted pistachios.